				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>XalmatElemental wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Random spawn timers for bosses only kthx. Normal exp mobs do not need a timer.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
"Normal exp mobs do not need a timer"
<br />

<br />
Hum, I don't know about that
<br />

<br />
Lets just do a devils advocate thing.
<br />

<br />
Part of the formula for EQ serial killing is to know when an event is going to happen.  We use this knowledge to prepare ourselves to deal with the event.  The most notable thing casters do is to get buffs in place vs being FoM.  Now if the time when an event is NOT known then we can not with assurance prepare ourselves for the event.
<br />

<br />
Anywho, I thought on this over the weekend and am not sure exactly how I feel about this.
<br />

<br />
I do suspect though, that a random spawning would tend to preserve a spawn's integrity.  Said more directly, it would tend to require us to continually break a spawn OR at the very least deal with unexpected add's.
<br />

<br />
Well at any rate it plays hell with EQWatcher</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
